# Local development environment for the DataLab-Web Python test suite.
#
# Copy this file to ``.env`` and adjust ``PYTHONPATH`` to point at your
# local sibling checkouts of Sigima and guidata (or remove those entries
# entirely if you installed them with ``pip install -r requirements-dev.txt``
# and want to use the wheels from PyPI).
#
# The Python interpreter itself is the project-local virtualenv created
# with::
#
#     py -3.11 -m venv .venv
#     .\.venv\Scripts\python -m pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
#
# ``scripts/run_with_env.py`` automatically picks up ``.venv\Scripts\python``
# when no ``PYTHON`` override is set. Set ``PYTHON=...`` here only if you
# want to bypass the project venv.
#
# Python 3.11+ is required: ``src/runtime/processor.py`` relies on
# ``isinstance(list[T], type)`` returning ``False``, which is broken under
# CPython 3.9 and 3.10 (both report ``True``) and was fixed in 3.11.

PYTHONPATH=.;..\Sigima;..\guidata
